Re: Why not make Charm, Mez, Fear easier to remove too?<br>
<br>
This isn't really the same thing. <br>
<br>
These spells are so debilitating that you wouldn't think twice about dispelling any affected player, regardless of the cost (losing other buffs). After all, what effect, other than instant death, can be worse than removing someone from the fight entirely, turning them against you and/or possibly bringing a nice train back to your group (Fear)? <br>
<br>
Slow is bad but it doesn't stop you fighting entirely and can be ignored by non-melee types anyway. Charm, Mez or Fear cannot be ignored, although with Fear the player might be halfway across the zone before you realise you need to dispel anyway and Mez tends to sort itself out (you get hit).<br>
<br>
I don't have a problem with the change to be honest. Look at it this way:<br>
<br>
If being Slowed was a major problem or &quot;challenge&quot; before (e.g. if you are a melee and the sole damage dealer in the group) then you would probably have been willing to lose all your buffs in order to get rid of it. It will most likely still take the same amount of time to get rid of that Slow now as it did via Dispel (it often takes several tries to successfully Cure).<br>
<br>
If being Slowed was NOT a major problem for you before (e.g. you are not a melee or there are other damage dealers in the group to cover you) then you probably won't be getting it removed by your healer now either (not worth their mana).<br>
<br>
It also forces someone to use up a valuable spell slot for a disease cure if they wish to take advantage of the new change which many won't be willing to do, even now.<br>
<br>
*shrug*<br>
<br>
As a finger wiggler I suppose I have no vested interest either way in this but I don't really think it dumbs anything down.<br>
<br>
